deck_excerpt: Two Archetypes which have absolultely 0 synergy with each other but somehow it works, and oh boy, does it work well.
deck_description:
Something I cooked up in Master Duel and decided to bring to the TCG. A fun and casual deck that can be really big threat if you know how to play it well.

Explanation of Every Key Card Incoming - Warning, This One's Big

==The P.U.N.K. Engine==

Noh-P.U.N.K. Ze Amin

The searcher of the deck. Pay 600 LP to add any P.U.N.K. monster from your deck to your hand. The effect to gain ATK is very important when chain-blocking (I'll get to that in the combo section)

Gagaku-P.U.N.K Wa Gon

Here to get the field spell from your deck by paying 600 LP (yes this is beneficial, I'll get to that when covering the extra deck)

Ukiyoe-P.U.N.K. Sharakusai

Lets you Fusion Summon on your turn by paying 600 LP or Synchro Summon on your opponent's by paying 600 LP. This is used to summon Rising Carp - which lets you combo further

Noh-P.U.N.K Deer Note

This is how you are able to make the level 8 Synchro monster. You do need another P.U.N.K monster in hand to activate its effect though, keep that in mind.

Noh-P.U.N.K Foxy Tune

Very important card. This is what gets you any of your level 3 P.U.N.K.s or Deer Note on the field without having to Normal Summon them. Very useful if you didn't draw Emergency Teleport.

Noh-P.U.N.K Ogre Dance

Basically Reinforcement of the Army but for P.U.N.K.

P.U.N.K. JAM Extreme Session

This is what allows you to draw more cards - up to 2 times per turn. VERY helpful for getting more P.U.N.K. cards or trying to get your Fur Hire engine. The effect to summon a P.U.N.K from your hand is a nice bonus too as it means you don't have to Normal Summon and you can save it for something else.

Emergency Teleport

Gets your level 3 P.U.N.K. monsters on the field. Beware of Ash Blossom.

 

==The Fur Hire Engine==

Beat, Bladesman Fur Hire

The monster searcher of Fur Hire. You can use its effect to summon any Fur Hire from hand and then use the other effect to search. Very powerful wehn combined with Rex, as it can be a chain block or be protected from As by Rex's effect.

Rex, Freight Fur Hire

Spell/Trap searcher of Fur Hire. The GY effect is important when combined with Donpa/Recon and Folgo as it allows you to interrupt your opponent's board while giving you another monster Fur Hire so you have 3 and can draw 3 from Folgo's effect.

Donpa, Marksman Fur Hire / Recon, Scout Fur Hire

These two do pretty much the same thing, but Donpa destroys face-up cards and Recon destroys face-down cards. Important with to use with Folgo.

Seal, Strategist Fur Hire

Lets you recycle your Fur Hire mosters from the GY to keep using.

Bravo, Fighter Fur Hire

Helpful for creating a very strong board of beefy Fur Hires - otherwise just another card in the combo

Filo, Messenger Fur Hire

Allows more recycling of Fur Hire monsters - this is Seal but better

Wiz, Sage Fur Hire

Gaining LP isn't that strong of an effect, but the negate is. Self explanatory.

Rafale, Champion Fur Hire

Pot of Prosperity for Fur Hire. The negate is a nice benefit too.

Reinforcement of the Army

For adding Beat to your hand and getting access to the Fur Hire engine.

Fossil Dig

For adding Rex to your hand.

Rookie Fur Hire

Allows you to go from the P.U.N.K engine into th Fur Hire engine, but you will not be able to summon Beat with this card, as you need to summon a monster with a level 1 higher or lower than that you tribute to activate it. Be careful in that this card locks you from attacking with anything that's not a Fur Hire monster for that turn.

Mayhem Fur Hire

Monster Reborn but for Fur Hire. Helpful with triggering Fur Hire effects on your opponent's turn (Try this with Folgo and Donpa/Recon)

 

==The Staples==

Pot of Prosperity

Lets you access more of your deck and therefore more parts of your combo - this will prevent you from drawing with the P.U.N.K. Field Spell though, so watch out for that and Ash, of course.

Called By the Grave

For stopping handtraps or GY effects. *Yes, Ash, I'm looking at you*

*I would put Reinforcement of the Army and Emergency Teleport here but they are only for one half of the deck each*

 

==The Extra Deck==

Ukiyoe-P.U.N.K. Rising Carp

Lets you Special Summon any two P.U.N.K. monster from your deck that are not level 8. Very helpful if you can't get Deer Note to go into Dragon Drive.

Ukiyoe-P.U.N.K. Amazing Dragon

A boss monster for P.U.N.K. which you can use to return cards your opponent controls to the hand - this could possibly return their entire field if you are lucky. Also this is Monster Reborn for P.U.N.K. but you can't use both effects on the same turn.

P.U.N.K. JAM Dragon Drive

This can search any level 3 P.U.N.K. monster, or if you want to play Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit you can add that instead - all for the mere cost of 600 LP. Also can resummon itself from the GY if your opponent responds to your P.U.N.K card or effect activation. Very nice.

Folgo, Justice Fur Hire

Able to summon ANY Fur Hire monster from your deck, but it cannot have the same type as any of Folgo's materials. The best effect is the draw effect, which you can use by destroying a opponent's card on the field. If you do, then you can draw 1 if you don't have 3 or more Fur Hire monsters with different names on your field, but if you do, then its basically equivalent to winning the lottery - more cards equals more combopieces.

Donner, Dagger Fur Hire

Helps with the Fur Hire combo and summoning Folgo. You can tribute itself to summon 2 Fur Hire monsters back to the field from your GY or from your hand. You can even use it to destroy a monster your opponent controls and a Fur Hire monster you control, even itself.

Psychic End Punisher

You know how the P.U.N.K. engine WANTS you to pay LP? Yeah, this is why that's beneficial for you. If you Synchro Summon it, then it's unaffected by your opponent's activated effects (EVEN NEGATES) while your LP are lower than theirs. It even has a way to lower your LP to try and keep its protection - and that way helps get rid of your opponent's problematic cards, at the cost of a monster you control and 1000 LP. This is very hard to get rid of without a Kaiju, Lava Golem, Sphere Mode, any other sort of tribute removal, or a floodgate. (Skill Drain will be your biggest threat here)

Clear Wing Synchro Dragon

Literally a Negate for level 5 or higher monsters on the field or to negate an effect that targets a level 5 or higher monster on the field. Can become a beefy beatstick but only use if neccessary.

Coral Dragon

A way to destroy your opponent's board and can draw you a card if it is sent from the field to the GY. Will rarely help you with combo plays - use at your own risk.

Metaphys Horus

A permanent negate for a face-up card on the field (because you're using an effect monster to Synchro Summon it). Will rarely help you with combo plays, but can save you in a pinch if you need a perma-negate

Stardust Charge Warrior

Coral Dragon, but draws a card on summon and can beat over a board by battle (if rarely) - Will rarely help you with combo plays but can help if you need more cards in your hand.

Naturia Beast

Unlimited Spell Negates. You need to use a P.U.N.K. tuner and Rex to summon this - that is the only way to summon it in this deck, but it can help with combo plays if needed. VERY powerful against decks that like to use lots of spells - e.g. Spright, Rikka Sunavalon, Branded Despia (Sometimes), Dragon Link, Kashtira (A little bit risky), and ESPECIALLY Runick and Sky Strikers.

Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder

Literally the easiest board wipe of all time. Make in Main Phase 2 using Downerd OR Fortune Tune and boom, you have an on-demand nuke.

Downerd Magician

Lets you get more materials for Zeus and you can Xyz Summon it on top of Fortune Tune.

Number 49: Fortune Tune

Lets you recycle your P.U.N.K. monsters or Beat to keep using. Also can act as a temporary wall as a last resort.

 

Last but not Least, the BEST waifu in this game

I:P Masqurena

Very easy to summon - you need any two non-link monsters. She makes it so any Link monster that used her as material cannot be destroyed by card effects. This effect is permanent, even if your opponent uses Called by the Grave on I:P, the protection is still applied. On top of that, you can Link Summon on your opponent's turn with her Quick Effect, letting you make Folgo on your opponent's turn.

 

I won't go over the side deck, as the cards are pretty self-explanatory. 

 

If you're still here after reading all that, thank you! It means a lot to me and shows that my hard work is worth the time and effort I put into these decks. I'll post another cool and unique deck when ever I get inspiration, or you can leave a suggestion in the comments.

CrankyBoy <3

deck_excerpt: Competitive Utopia Deck for going against Kash, Lab, Branded, Spright, etc
deck_description:
This variant of the utopia deck is the current iteration after the June 5th 2023 banlist. The deck lost 2 copies of circular and 1 copy of #89 mindhacker. Overall, these were moderate hits with the biggest hit being the loss of #89 which means the deck loses access to sniping out troublesome cards from the opponent’s extra deck.

I have updated the deck to be more inline with the current meta decks of the format mostly Kashtira, Branded, Labrynth, and the various Spright variants that players will mostly face at the top competitive level. The deck that I did not mention is dragon link, bystials are this decks biggest counter and Dragonlink is this deck’s most unfavorable match up.

For side decking

Side decking wise this deck remains most consistent when swapping out roughly 6 cards that being 2 copies of Zexal Construction, 3 copies of small world, and 1 copy of Pankrotops. The cards one will mostly side in will be 3 copies of triple tactics thrust, 1 copy of evenly match, 1 copy of raigeki, and 1 copy of feather duster. With this ratio including the pots of prosperity for consistency boost will mean that in a 6-card hand you will open 1 essential board breaker card 92% of the time.

Pot of prosperity

In this current build pot of prosperity is less punishing and can be used to look at the top 3 to get what you need roughly 77% of the time. Even post side and going second pot of prosperity for 3 generally will find what you need, hitting for 6 is too much of a gamble and sacrifices far too much follow up.

Combo lines and tips

This deck has not changed very much from its previous iteration found here: https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/utopia-deck-326651

all of these combo lines are still so use the link for refrence when learning combos and tricks. The only new addition to the combo is the Sakitama Aratama monsters. The main strength of the 2 new spirit monsters is that aratama is not a OPT searcher and is a 1 card r4nk that uses the normal summon. Aratama makes small world slightly better as it means small world goes from a -1 to a net 0 if choosing to search aratama. Though generally small world will still most often be used to search pieces to make kali yuga or mathmech cards to set up an early omni-negate. Aratama has the additonal bonus of being a Dark Fiend type monster which no other monster in this deck shares this stats making aratama an excellent small world bridge. Thus the spirit cards make the Deck slightly more normal summon reliant compared to past iterations but small world becomes a much more flexible card as a result.

deck_name: star warrior anti kashira master duel
deck_description: let beat tier 1 kashira deck in master duel.
Main focus is to get Supreme King Z-arc out an destroy your oppenents board.

Swordsoul with True Kings as an alternative to Tenyi. Each True King is designed not necessarily for card advantage but replacement, so it takes longer for you to run out of resources. The same idea is behind Tenyi with being allowed to banish them from the grave for a second use from a single card. When you don't happen to get a replacement effect from two different attribute Kings being destroyed the True Kings offer disruption with Lithosagm and Mariamne, and escapes with Bahrastos and Agnimizud. Your Fire and Water are invaluable in games for getting the edge at the right time over your opponent if possible, or just allowing you to be able to even play the game to begin with. Hyperyton helps in situations with Dinos to also stop Miscellaneousaurus or other effects but sadly cannot stop anything during your turn. Enterblathnir is usually used with Psy-Framelord turn one if you go that route to have your opponent start with four cards their first turn. Book of eclipse has been good for match ups against Kashtira, but I've also noticed that Altergeists when they can't have their effects negated are better off face down. Codebreaker is the out to Bagooska instead of running Bagooska, you don't worry about it's effect getting negated by an impermanence or veiler or Mourner like with Dagger Fur Hire but it can be countered by other back row. It's also needed to get over a knighmare Iblee since Links are going to be forced to be played sometimes yet we don't get three more extra deck and side deck cards to accommodate such a change. There's three Baxia for when you're forced to open with Taia, use Taia to send Mo Ye to the grave then Baxia usually would destroy itself to summon it and you still have two more to shuffle up to four of the opponents cards back. Twin twisters can replace two of your blackouts when you're dealing with pesky field spells etc. and cannot use Bahrastos' or Baxia's effects. Lastly about Crossout in the side deck there. Well, if you ask me while it's playable, I think every side deck needs three for that potential mirror match. Good luck and have fun!

Making use of the new "Synchron" support, the upcoming "Horus" cards go on an "Adventure". The recently released Synchron cards, Assault Synchron and Revolution Synchron, are excellent additions to any Synchro-based decks and even better at enabling certains strategies, such as how in the OCG, Assault Synchron is being used with cards like the "Bystials", as they work very well with Level 6s and 8s, to make powerful cards like Chaos Ruler, the Chaotic Magical Dragon, which is currently banned in the TCG, and Baronne de Fleur, a Synchro Staple. Speaking of Level 8 monsters that are recently released and are easily summonable, the Horus cards coming in AGOV (Age of Overlord) do just that. On top of that, the Horus Engine is fairly small, and they don't use their normal summon, so the Brave/Adventurer Engine slots in perfectly here, as it adds an easily accessible omni-negate for no cost.

I have tested this list for a couple days now and looking for some ideas on how to improve the list

Blue-Eyes Jet Dragon is an excellent piece of Legacy Support for the "Blue-Eyes" archetype, as it made the deck much better, but not broken. However, the card can be used as a small engine in other decks to enable it, like Dragon Shrine and The White Stone of Ancients. Jet Dragon provides destruction protection for other cards you control and can summon itself from your hand or grave when any card on the field is destroyed, which synergizes fairly well with the "Labrynth" archetype, as they utilize Lovely Labrynth of the Silver Castle, Archfiend's Ghastly Glitch, and Dogmatika Punishment that are all easily accesible cards which destroy. White Stone is also easily discardable thanks to the Labrynth Furniture, Labrynth Chandraglier and Labrynth Stovie Torbie, and can profit you during the End Phase by summoning a Blue-Eyes from your deck, granted you aren't locked by Welcome Labrynth.

deck_excerpt: The Weather Painters are back from being Banished
deck_description:
"The Weather Painters" are an archetype of Fairies of all different attributes across the Rainbow, and they utlilize their archetypal backrow, the "Canvases" to give their monsters additional effects, such as how The Weather Snowy Canvas adds another Weather card from your deck to your hand, but because these Canvases banish for cost, and their Main Deck monsters don't have too exceptional effects while on the field, they can easily utilize floodgates, such as Skill Drain or Macro Cosmos, without much detriment to their own.

The boss monsters of the deck, The Weather Painter Rainbow and The Weather Painter Moonbow, are both Link-3 monsters which, like the Canvases, give effects to Weather Painter monsters they point to, like how Rainbow gives them an omni-negate, and Moonbow makes them an Interdimensional Matter Transporter on legs. Moonbow can reborn a banished Weather Painter monster upon being Link Summoned, and if it's destroyed, can summon a Rainbow from your Extra Deck, and Rainbow can also negate an opponent's special summon by send itself to the grave if it was Link Summoned, and shares the same effect of the Main Deck Weather Painters to summon itself the turn after it was banished by a Weather effect.

Category: Tournament Meta Deck Master duel

 

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

 

Creator: Kim Minsung

(Disclaimer: This deck works better, if you go first and if your opponent played at most two cards from their hand. If they play "Maxx C", as long as they don't have any interruption during your turn or next turn such as "Super Polymerization" and alike, it will be piece of cake.)

Greetings! This is a mixture of Mill and Burn deck, with "Present Card" acting as milling and "Magical Thorn" acting as burning. Let me explain how:

 

- Draw your deck until you find all trap cards. Don't forget to play "Gold Moon Coin" in advance to give your opponent two extra cards right into their hands.

- Set all traps. End your turn. When it's your opponent's turn of Draw Phase, they should have 8 cards, provided they didn't quick play anything.

- It's time to activate all traps even during Draw Phase of your opponent. First, change "Activation Confirmation" to "Switch+Hold" and set to "ON" in-game. You can edit to "Switch+Hold" in "Duel" section of settings page. Then, activate traps in order as mentioned below:

  1. Present Card
  2. The Gift of Greed
  3. Magical Thorn
  4. Magical Thorn
  5. Magical Thorn

- What is going to happen is that...

  • Whenever you send a card from your opponent's hand into their GY, they will take 500 damage for each thanks to "Magical Thorn". We have three of them active, so it will be 1500 damage for each.
  • Our opponent had 8 cards, now it will be increased by 2 with "The Gift of Greed", to make it 10 cards in total.
  • "Present Card" will deliver all cards your opponent has into their GY. So, damage output will be 1500 x 10 = 15000, leading into the OTK.
  • You can watch the deck in action by clicking here!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contact Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Present Card" + "Ravenous" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR!

- "Into The Void" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Link Bound" is given for free, if you have picked "Link Generation". Thus, 30 SR is saved!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 510 SR and 30 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_name: A Beginner's Guide to ABC Synchron (August 2023)
deck_excerpt: This old fan favourite deck, ABC machines have new toys that boost their power!
deck_description:
Revolution Synchron combined with the relatively recent unbanning of Ancient Fairy Dragon has singlehandedly breathed new life into the ABC Dragon Buster strategy. 
 
Revolution Synchron + any level 4 (ABC monsters, Adventure Token, etc.) can make Ancient Fairy Dragon (AFD) allowing for extra extension and a search for another field spell! Since the deck revolves around multiple field spells, AFD can bridge into the Therion cards for another negate + extension, since Therion Regulus equips an ABC monster from the GY. 
 
The synergy of ABC, Adventure, Therion and Ancient Fairy Dragon (made possible with Revolution Synchron) allows the strategy to end on a nearly unbreakable board with 7+ negates/interruptions, while the ABC cards provide ample follow-up for next turn!
 
(Shoutout to Yacine656 and MST.TV from Youtube where I took inspiration to make this deck-guide from. If you want more information, be sure to watch their videos on the ABC strategy!)
  • Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING 

 

Forming the main body of the strategy, the ABC cards compose of 13 cards: 3 B-Buster Drake, 2 C-Crush Wyvern, 2 A-Assault Core, 1 Union Driver, 3 Union Hangar, 1 Terraforming and 1 Set Rotation.  In the Extra Deck there are 2 ABC-Dragon Buster. 

 

Functioning as a supporting engine to the ABC cards, the ADVENTURE package is composed of 8 cards: 3 Water Enchantress, 2 Rite of Aramesir, 1 Fateful Adventure, 1 Dracoback, and 1 Wandering Gryphon Rider. 

 

The THERION package is tiny since it is highly searchable: 2 Therion Discolossseum and 2 Regulus. In the Extra Deck, there is 1 Springans Merrymaker and 1 Gigantic Champion Sargas so they can search out Regulus. 

 

The small but impactful SYNCHRON package is only composed of three cards: 3 Revolution Synchron. In the Extra Deck There is 1 AFD and 1 Crystal Wing. 

 

The rest of the cards are STAPLES. 3 Pot of Prosperity is used to increase the consistency of this deck (it's kind of bricky). 10+ handtraps are used in this deck so it can play second after weakening/stopping your opponent's strategy. 

 

COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN 

 
Like most combo heavy decks, ABC's gameplan is to set-up as many interruptions as possible (up to 7!) while accruing tons of advantage and resources for itself. This deck excels at going first and it's brickiness is somewhat fixed due to how easy it is to access AFD through Revolution Synchron and AFD searches for this deck's main fieldspell starter, Union Hangar. Going second, this deck has a difficult time playing through interruption, but can easily set-up Bagooska in a pinch. 

The entire ABC combo line is now protected by Crystal Wing through Revolution Synchron and the Adventure Package - so if you open with either of these engines, you can protect your main combo. These combos are also featured on Yacine656's channel if you want to check out a video on them. Here are this deck's ABC combos: 
 
Union Hangar + Revolution Synchron = Crystal Wing's monster negate/destroy + Regulus' omni-negate + I:P Masquerena's quick effect link (Underworld Goddess, Knightmare Unicorn, Apollousa) + ABC Dragon Buster's banish and summon from the banish pile of ABC monsters. (7 interruptions + follow-up!)
  1. Activate Union Hangar. Search for B-Buster Drake. 
  2. Normal Summon B-Buster Drake. Activate Union Hangar's trigger effect to equip B-Buster Drake with Union Driver from deck. 
  3. Activate Union Driver's effect to equip from deck C-Crush Wyvern.
  4. Special summon C-Crush Wyvern from backrow. 
  5. Synchro summon AFD using Revolution Synchron from hand. 
  6. Search A-Assault Core from B-Buster Drake's trigger effect. 
  7. Activate AFD's effect to destroy your field spell Union Hangar to search Discolosseum. 
  8. Activate Discolosseum to search Therion Regulus. 
  9. Activate Revolution Synchron's effect to summon itself from the GY as a level 1 tuner. 
  10. Activate AFD's effect to summon A-Assault Core from hand. 
  11. Synchro summon Crystal Wing using AFD + Revolution Synchron (That's the 5th summon, protecting you vs. Nibiru). 
  12. Special summon from hand Regulus by equipping B-Buster Drake from the GY. 
  13. Special summon B-Buster Drake from the backrow.
  14. Link summon Platinum Gadget using B-Buster Drake + A-Assault Core. 
  15. CL1 B-Buster Drake to search for another B-Buster Drake from deck and CL2 A-Assault Core to retrieve B-Buster Drake from GY. 
  16. Activate Platinum Gadget's effect to summon B-Buster Drake from hand. 
  17. Link summon I:P Masquerena using B-Buster Drake and C-Crush Wyvern. 
  18. CL1 B-Buster Drake to search for A-Assault Core from deck, CL2 C-Crush Wyvern to summon to B-Buster Drake from hand. 
  19. Special summon ABC Dragon Buster by banishing the A, B and C monsters from GY. 
  20. Activate B-Buster Drake to equip itself to ABC Dragon buster, rendering it immune to spell cards. 
Union Hangar + Rite of Aramesir = Wandering Gryphon Rider's omni-negate + ABC Dragon Buster's banish and summon from the banish pile of ABC monsters. (2 interruptions + follow-up)
  1. Activate Union Hangar. Search for B-Buster Drake.
  2. Activate Rite of Aramesir to summon an Adventure Token and place Fateful Adventure in the backrow. 
  3. Normal Summon B-Buster Drake. CL1 Union Hangar to equip B-Buster Drake with Union Driver from deck, CL2 Fateful Adventure to search for Dracoback from deck. 
  4. Activate Fateful Adventure to search for Wandering Gryphon Rider while discarding Dracoback. 
  5. Equip Dracoback from GY to Adventure Token and summon Gryphon Rider from hand. 
  6. Activate Union Driver effect to equip from deck A-Assault Core.
  7. Special summon A-Assault Core from backrow. 
  8. Link summon Platinum Gadget using B-Buster Drake and A-Assault Core. 
  9. B-Buster Drake searches for C-Crush Wyvern from deck. (Don't activate A-Assault Core's trigger effect here, or else you can't make ABC Dragon Buster!)
  10. Special summon C-Crush Wyvern from hand using Platinum Gadget's effect. 
  11. Special summon ABC Dragon Buster by banishing the A, B and C monsters from GY. 
Therion Discolosseum + Revolution Synchron + Rite of Aramesir = Crystal Wing's monster negate/destroy + Regulus' omni-negate + Apollousa's 3 monster negates, ABC Dragon Buster's banish and summon from the banish pile of ABC monsters. (6 interruptions + follow-up!)
  1. Activate Rite of Aramesir to summon an Adventure Token and place Fateful Adventure in the backrow. 
  2. Activate Therion Discolosseum to search for Regulus from deck. 
  3. Synchron summon AFD using Adventure Token + Revolution Synchron. 
  4. Fateful Adventure's trigger effect searches Dracoback from deck. 
  5. AFD destroys Discolosseum to search for Union Hangar from deck. 
  6. Activate Union Hangar to search for B-Buster Drake from deck. 
  7. Special summon B-Buster from hand using AFD's effect. 
  8. Activate Union Hangar's trigger effect to equip B-Buster Drake with Union Driver from deck.
  9. Activate Revolution Synchron's effect to summon itself from the GY as a level 1 tuner.
  10. Synchro summon Crystal Wing using AFD + Revolution Synchron (That's the 5th summon, protecting you vs. Nibiru).
  11. Activate Union Driver effect to equip from deck A-Assault Core.
  12. Special summon A-Assault Core from backrow.
  13. Link summon Platinum Gadget using B-Buster Drake and A-Assault Core.
  14. CL1 B-Buster Drake searches for C-Crush Wyvern from deck. CL2 A-Assault Core to retrieve B-Buster Drake from GY.
  15. Special summon C-Crush Wyvern from hand using Platinum Gadget's effect.
  16. Special summon from hand Regulus by equipping A-Assault Core from the GY.
  17. Special summon A-Assault Core from backrow. 
  18. Link summon I:P Masqurena using A-Assault + C-Crush. 
  19. CL1 A-Assault Core to retrieve from GY C-Crush, CL2 C-Crush to summon B-Buster Drake from hand. 
  20. Normal summon C-Crush. 
  21. Link summon Apollousa using I:P Masquerena, B-Buster and C-Crush Wyvern. 
  22. B-Buster Drake's trigger effect searches for another B-Buster Drake from deck. 
  23. Special summon ABC Dragon Buster by banishing the A, B and C monsters from GY. 
  24. (Extra action, not needed in the combo) Search with Fateful Adventure Water Enchantress and discard her. Banish her from GY to search for Rite of Aramesir from deck. 

GENERAL TIPS

  • While piloting this deck, I discovered that it's REALLY easy to misplay. Certain actions (Like A-Assault recovering an ABC from GY) prevents certain plays from happening (like ensuing there are at least 1 of each ABC monster in the GY to special summon ABC Dragon Buster). It's important to practice a lot with this deck so you can memorize the combos! 
  • This deck's combos are different with every hand. Be sure to practice the combos to know which combos are optimal for whatever cards you open! 
  • If you get Droll'd or Shifter'd, make Bagooska and pass turn so you can wait out the turn-stopping lingering effect which stops the main combo cold. 
  • Going first, this deck has a high power ceiling and a strong board most decks would have difficulty cracking. Going second however, this deck central combo doesn't really play through much interruption. 
  • Despite this deck's consistency boosted by Revolution Synchron and AFD, it's still somewhat bricky. This deck features 4 bricks out of a 40 card deck, so there is a relatively large chance you draw into one of them.
  • For paying the cost of Pot of Prosperity, keep in mind which Extra Deck cards you'll use for the duration of the duel. My favourite 6 Extra Deck cards to banish are Knightmare Phoenix, Knightmare Unicorn, Underworld Goddess, Avramax, Springans Merrymaker and Gigantic Champion Sargas. 
  • While going second, play the Adventure package first to bait out interruption before going for the main combo. Gryphon's omni-negate and Dracoback's target bounce puts immense pressure on your opponent to react. 
  • Before activating ABC Dragon Buster's triple summon from the banished pile, be sure to use Regulus' or Gryphon Rider's omni-negate first so you clear a space on your board for the summon of three monsters at once. 
     
    Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
 

CONCLUDING REMARKS

 
Any ABC monster coupled with Revolution Synchron makes Ancient Fairy Dragon does wonders for the deck! AFD bridging Union Hangar <-> Therion Discolosseum means that either fieldspell and its associated strategy is easily accessible. Crystal Wing before the 5th summon coupled with Regulus and before the main combo renders most handtraps useless against the ABC strategy, especially it's old nemesis, Nibiru! (Shoutout to MST.TV and Yacine656 for their combos/decklists)
 
I'm a mecha and gundam FANATIC. I love machines bristling with weaponry, explosives, and missiles. Now I can bring that mechanical love into yugioh duels with ABC Synchron! ABC Synchron scratches that itch to play with machines competitively since it stars ABC Dragon Buster, Regulus and with it's most recent addition, Revolution Synchron! Now this old fan favourite has a new lease on life in the cutthroat competitive 2023 meta!
 
GLHF Duelists!

deck_excerpt: Half a deck plus half a deck is a full deck right

deck_description:
Hello there! In this deck, we will OTK our opponent with the help of a trio of cards. They are "Treasure Panda" + "Arcana Force" + C6, which will be done with using "Diamond Dust". Know that by cutting these cards, the remaining template can be used in any C6 OTK shenanigans you can plan in the future. I will be also sharing example ideas you can try with in "Side Deck" section but you are welcome to try anything you desire:

  • Nemeses Umbrella + Nemeses Corridor
  • Diamond Dust

Also, I put 2 x "Apprentice Illusion Magician", in case you don't have/like Bystials as Level 6 extenders for C6, seen in "Side Deck". You can use Magicians outside of this deck. Without further ado, let's get started.

 

Gameplan

1) While drawing your deck, bring forth both Bystials to XYZ summon Number 6. At one point, either bring forth 2 x Cthuguas to follow-up with Number 60 or with Cthugua + Corridor. Since you will be banishing two monsters via Bystials, it won't be a problem for you to pull out "Nemeses Corridor".

2) With Number 6 on the battlefield, play "Argent Chaos Force" to bring forth C6. Meanwhile, you should use Number 60 to draw cards and give it to your opponent with "Shien's Spy".

  • After you have gifted Number 60 to your opponent, use the first ability of C6 to steal Number 60 and equip onto C6. Then, use its second ability to set your opponent's LP to 100. Just don't play any "Upstart Goblin" afterwards and you will be good to go.

3) When you have "Light Barrier" present, trigger the ability of "Angel O1" to bring forth "Arcana Force". Then, follow-up with Tribute Summoning "Arcana Force". Pick the outcome as heads for "Arcana Force" to always skip your opponent's turn, at the cost of delivering two of your monsters to your GY.

4) Then, bring forth "Nemeses Umbrella" and set "Diamond Dust". End your turn whenever you are ready but before that, change "Activation Confirmation" to "Switch+Hold" and set to "ON" in-game. You can edit to "Switch+Hold" in "Duel" section of settings page.

5) Send two of your monsters except "Nemeses Umbrella" and "Arcana Force" to GY. Don't forget, this was needed to skip your opponent's turn.

6) It's your time to shine bright like diamonds while offering your opponent its rust. During your Draw Phase, you can simply activate "Diamond Dust" to finish your opponent by destroying "Nemeses Umbrella". Your opponent had 100 LP thanks to C6 and you dealt 500 damage. Thus, it's lethal.

  • Can you just punch your opponent right into the face without using "Diamond Dust"? Absolutely! Yet, this deck is a proof of concept as to how to beat your opponent with C6 via LP reduction like Earthbound Greater Linewalker.

 

- You can watch the deck in action by clicking here!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contact Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Arcana Force XXI - The World" + "Light Barrier" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 30 UR!

- "Argent Chaos Force" + "Number 6" + "Number C6" can be found within "Timeworn Legacies" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 60 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Link Bound" is given for free, if you have picked "Link Generation". Thus, 30 SR is saved!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 480 SR and 120 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!
